You mean this one?<p><pre><code>    int binary_search_pow2(const int a[], int len, int key) {
        int i = 0, step;
        for (step = len / 2; step > 0; step >>= 1)
            if (a[i | step] <= key)
                i |= step;
        return i;
    }
</code></pre>
I thought that only worked for power-of-two sized arrays.
